# Language Guide

## Common Code Style and Optimization Guidelines

- Refactor repeated logic into reusable functions.
- Don’t be backward compatible, Write reusable code logic as much as possible.
- Prefer object destructuring when accessing and using properties.
- Use consistent, descriptive naming; avoid obscure abbreviations.
- Use semantically meaningful variable, function, and class names.
- **Replace magic numbers or strings with well-named constants.**
- Keep meaningful code comments; do not remove them when applying edits. Update comments when behavior changes.
- Ensure Language comments accurately reflect the implementation.
- Look for opportunities to simplify or modernize code with the latest Language features where it improves clarity.
- Defer formatting to tooling; ignore purely formatting-only issues and autofixable lint problems.

## Project Specific Code Style and Optimization Guidelines

- Read kline server code style: @kline-server/.cursor/rules/java.mdc
- Read kline web ui code style: @kline-web-ui/.cursor/rules/language.mdc
- When writing tests, avoid writing simple test examples, such as not checking an object's properties immediately after it is created.
